Thank Back to Top SAVE OUR PLANET…ONE PUP AT A TIME Made in the USA © All Rights Reserved | Privacy Policy   Sustainability — Pooch Paper Sign In My Account Home Shop Our Story Sustainability Press Contact Us Sign In My Account Home Shop Our Story Sustainability Press Contact Us SUSTAINABILITY STARTS WITH YOU Made in the USA, Pooch Paper is a recycled, bleached paper alternative to plastic dog waste Our sheets are % biodegradable, % compostable and are manufactured using renewable Our , oil and grease resistant coating is made naturally during the pulp drying process in order to ensure your doggie’s doodie remains inside the paper and not on your hand! Most manufactured products contain PFAS chemicals that are nearly impossible to break down Pooch Paper is Thank you for considering Pooch Paper as a plastic alternative in helping us save our planet one PUP at a time! There are an estimated billion pounds of doggie doodie dropped each year in the While not all dog parents pick up after their dogs, roughly ten million tons of dog waste and over million plastic doggie bags end up in landfills each Most doggie parents have become sensitive to the growing awareness around plastics, and have begun to consider how dog waste bags play into this environmental Some pet parents have chosen to “up cycle,” or reuse plastic bags that come from the grocery market, for Others use plastic bags, which purport to be The latest initiative to hit the dog waste bag market includes While all of these efforts are one step closer to being , there still remains one common denominator across all of these categories: plastic . Research suggests dog owners use more than million plastic bags for dog waste Plastic is generally not biodegradable - it can take over years to degrade, if it ever Some bags are manufactured as , meaning that a formula called EPI is added during the manufacturing process to enable the plastic to break down However, often do not fully Instead, they break down into millions of particles that enter the air we breathe, the water we drink and ultimately the food supply we Such particles may, among other things, carry toxic or carcinogenic chemicals used in making the plastic, or they can act as a carrier for pathogens and heavy Our planet and our pups are made to be loved! In National Geographic released a study, Microplastics are Raining Down from the Sky , following an air quality research project conducted in remote mountain locations furthering this In , Consumer Reports published their findings suggesting that humans ingest a credit amount of plastic each week due to increasing If standard plastic and are dangerous to sustainability, what about bioplastics? Bioplastics have recently entered the marketplace in an effort to replace fossil fuels with renewable resources such as corn, starch and other proteins in the manufacturing In this case, bioplastics are capable of breaking down under controlled environmental conditions such as exposure to sunlight and moisture - two factors nearly impossible to guarantee or control when disposed of in a Additionally, the combination of plastic and animal waste amidst compressed garbage in landfills results in the emission of methane gas into the air - which, as a greenhouse gas, absorbs the sun’s heat, thereby warming the atmosphere and adversely affecting the The release of large quantities of methane gas is especially problematic in studies that show that, within the first two years of emission, methane can be measured around times more potent than carbon STUDIES INDICATE HUMANS INGEST A CREDIT AMOUNT OF MICROPLASTIC EACH WEEK Replace your daily, plastic dog bags and help save our planet ONE PUP AT A TIME! What is an pet parent supposed to do? We invite you to conduct your own research related to best practices and consider changing your daily plastic consumable to Pooch Paper! For further reading, Rose Seemann’s Pet Poo Pocket Guide provides a comprehensive “how-to” instruction for safely composting and recycling pet Where is Pooch Paper manufactured? Our paper, packaging and fulfillment processes are all sourced and conducted in the The vast majority of our pulp is sourced from the as well as Canada (with traces from Sweden, Norway, Finland, Estonia, Latvia, Poland, England and Spain). We build income properties in These are also known as Accessory Dwelling Units (ADUs). Normally we convert existing garages into apartments – but we can build freestanding units from scratch as These projects can either be funded by us, or by What is an Accessory Dwelling Unit (ADU)? An ADU is a permitted structure on your property that can be used to legally house a It’s a fancy way to say “granny flat,” “in-law suite,” “backyard apartment,” Most people who have an ADU and rent it out call it a money machine 🙂 Are backyard units legal? Yes, rental units are legal in California – now more than As of January , California made it much easier to permit and build them in most residential yards (all R1 zoned properties and anything larger, like R2, ) – whether converting existing structures like garages, or building from the ground If I have an unpermitted structure already, can Yardsworth make it a legal rental unit? We will do all of the necessary work to get your unpermitted structure built and permitted properly, and ready for a legal Can my home support a backyard rental? We hope so! Usually all you need is an extra – square feet of space in your The more space you have, the more flexibility you have for providing a private yard or patio for the guests tenants. Does Yardsworth offer custom designs, units, build above the garage, ? Yes, we can do custom If you are funding the project yourself, then think of us as your for any type of construction However, if you choose to use Yardsworth’s Funding Program, then we will build the rental to match the rental income potential of your particular yard and We’ll figure out the best structure once we visit and inspect your Program Details How much will it cost to build my rental unit with Yardsworth? Yardsworth covers the costs to design, permit and build the If you prefer to pay for the project yourself, no problem! The cost of a typical garage conversion is $99,000 and will include ALL project costs (architecture, engineering, permitting, construction, appliances, ) for a rental that is What if I decide to sell my home? No The rental unit belongs to you – so you sell it with the It’s a great boost having an extra unit can increase your property value by $150,000 or When you sell your home, our contract ends, but the tenant gets to stay and simply starts paying rent to the new Will my property taxes increase? Yes, your property taxes will increase a small amount (1% – % of just the construction value, not an entire home ) – which is minimal compared to the $5,000 – $10,000 per year you will earn from having it rented with How will my insurance be affected? We recommend that you notify your insurance company that there is a tenant living in the They may increase your annual premium by $20-35. What amenities does a Yardsworth ADU have? Yardsworth apartments are designed to rent at a premium with , modern finishes, custom countertops and cabinets, Whirlpool appliances — washer dryer, range, oven, and microwave, A C & Heat mini split system — and all the layout features of a How long will construction take? 2 months for design, engineering and 2 months of construction (yes, that is VERY fast 🙂 ) Renting the ADU Do I get to select my tenant? Yes! Yardsworth will list the unit on top rental sites, conduct showings, and collect rent We run credit and background checks and deliver you up to 5 qualified You may choose the tenant that feels right for you and your family (of course, abiding by all state and federal Fair Housing laws). Where will the tenant park? In almost all cases, homeowners have no obligation to provide a parking space for the tenant – street parking typically Who pays for utilities? All utilities are separately metered and billed to the tenant, except for water sewer trash, which will remain covered by the What happens if I have issues with the tenant? Yardsworth is the property manager of your rental unit, so we manage the relationship with the tenant and any needs or issues they may If there are any problems with either the homeowner or the tenant, each party reports to Yardsworth to handle resolving the Are pets allowed? No, the tenant cannot keep pets in the unit – though service animals are permitted under Fair Housing Have additional questions? The desk was one of her favorite possessions, but she knew that if the proceeds from its sale raised money to rescue children from this horror, that would be worth more to her than the desk She wondered if other people found themselves in similar situations, wanting to help charities but without available Would they also be interested in selling heirlooms to contribute to this cause? She began vetting the idea with her friends in media, business, finance, Hollywood, sports, high society, and even They all agreed: Donating something of value to be auctioned with the proceeds going to stop human trafficking would be far more meaningful than owning any particular Mitzi put the final piece into place to bring this bold idea to life by finding an auction house that would generously agree to hold an auction for Win This Fight and waive their commission Our Mission , Vision , and Values Win This Fight was established with a goal to raise $100 million over two years through the generosity of donors gifting valuable possessions such as art, jewelry, cars, china, collections, and boats to save the lives of thousands of victims and prevent the trafficking of thousands Today, more than volunteers and donors have pledged to support our quest to stop human trafficking for good! Will you join us ? Our Mission Win This Fight seeks to support the United Nations’ goal to eradicate human trafficking by by meeting two of the greatest needs of the community: additional funding and additional Our Vision The International Labour Organization (ILO) estimates that there are million victims of human trafficking globally, and further, ILO estimates that forced labor and human trafficking is a $150 billion industry There are already ,000 organizations combating labor and sex trafficking around the To benefit those efforts, Win This Fight is raising awareness and raising funding to support the good works they are already Through our unique gifting opportunities , generous donors designate the trafficking organization to receive the sales proceeds of their item auctioned in live or online The live auctions will feature donated items in the price Online auctions will feature donations of all Through our leadership team , staff, and volunteers , Win This Fight is passionate, dedicated, and motivated to be awareness advocates, boots on the ground, ears in the crowd, hands on the paddles, and the voices of our Those most vulnerable, who were lured, kidnapped, beaten, manipulated, abused, and trafficked, do not have a While they are locked up, they need us to work together and Win This Fight … for GOOD! Our Values Humanity: Every human being deserves to be treated with respect, dignity, and Every human being deserves a life free from abuse, assault, and forced labor or sexual For those who have no voice, we rally on their behalf to secure and distribute resources to organizations that make the most significant difference to Win This Global Collaboration: Win This Fight is a global and bipartisan organization that includes all those who share our passion, mission, vision, values, and dedication to STOP human trafficking…for GOOD! Our People: Our team and partner organizations are the most important resources to Win This Without them, this gargantuan effort does not have legs, our victims do not get rescued, and human trafficking does not Human Rights: The few paid staff and hundreds of volunteers of Win This Fight uphold the human rights of respect, dignity, honor, and Teamwork: We value the expertise, strengths, natural talents, and skillsets our members and volunteers share with us, and we build people and teams based on what they most enjoy and what they can best Strengths: Integrity, inclusivity, generosity, open communication, productivity, best practices, and appreciation are the pillars of our organization and the forefront of how we work together to become Service: We keep, at the front of our mind, the terror and darkness our victims face and the hope to end human trafficking and forced labor through fundraising And we use those visions to propel us forward each and e
